{
  "stem": "25912.5",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And one of the guys, one of the officers in this mission, knew me from the Warsaw Rising again, recognized me.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they got us a couple of rooms and some food.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And our two guides set off to Linz to tell my father and his friend who was with him where we were.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And two days later, early in the morning, a 15-ton military truck arrived with my father and his friend and the driver, loaded us.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "First time he had seen me since I was nine and 1/2.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we went from Pilsen to Munich, where we stayed the night in the American Officers' Club.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was heaven-- continuous donuts and coffee.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] But Munich was, again, like Warsaw-- complete devastation.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean, this was the best hotel the [INAUDIBLE], which was standing, or partly standing.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was the American Officers' Club.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But the rest of Munich was absolute ruin.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And from then, we drove to Italy-- my father had documents to get us into Italy-- and took us to Milan, where we stayed, I think, for about a week, being dressed and fed and listening to stories.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And all this time, we're asking about George, and was George going to be with us for Christmas?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father said, oh, he's in Africa-- maybe.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We'll, you know, it depends.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we still believed that he was all right.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And after a week, week or 10 days, in Milan, which was absolute heaven-- suddenly, I could go and have a new pair of shoes and clothes, and sleep in a very comfortable bed, and eat as much as I wanted, and have fruits and oranges, and things which I hadn't seen since before the war.",
      "word_count": 56
    }
  ],
